HEADWORD: Meticulous
<hw>Me*tic"u*lous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>meticulosus</ets>, fr. <ets>metus</ets> fear: cf. F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧ticuleux</ets>.]</ety> <def>Timid; fearful.</def>
<mark>[archaic]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Taking great care to get every detail correct;
working thoroughly and with precision; <as>as, <ex>meticulous</ex>
workmanship</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Me*tic"u*lous*ly</wf>,
